margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"=
>Evo 2 is a new AI model from a team at the Arc Institute that learns the &=
#8220;language&#8221; of DNA, allowing it to predict the effect of mutation=
s, design new sequences, and influence gene expression.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">The=
 model is trained on 9.3 trillion DNA base pairs across all domains of life=
=2E It predicts whether mutations are h=
armful or benign without specific trai=
ning on human disease data, outperforming specialized models and accurately=
 handling noncoding mutations&#8212;suggesting it has internalized DNA&#821=
7;s fundamental principles. That&#8217;s right: Evo 2 has learned the core =
rules of DNA on its own, allowing it to predict genetic effects across all =
life forms without being specifically trained on human disease data.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-siz=
e: 16px;"><strong>Evo 2 can create entire DNA sequences,</strong><span> lik=
e those for mitochondria and bacteria, in a way that looks natural. It can =
also control how genes are turned on or off by influencing DNA structure. A=
s a test, researchers used it to encode Morse code into DNA, showing its po=
tential for designing custom genetic systems.</span></p><p style=3D"margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>=
